This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new exploration strategy for deep reinforcement learning using an ensemble of Q-functions. It also involves adapting algorithms from the bandit setting to the Q-learning setting, which is a common approach in machine learning research. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DL (Deep Learning), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control), as these fields often involve applications of reinforcement learning and exploration strategies.
